{"timestamp": "2026-06-01T10:04:21.454283", "event": "AGENT_OBSERVATION", "data": {"step": 7, "tool": "web_search", "args": "DS1307 datasheet I2C address", "observation": "Kết quả web cho 'DS1307 datasheet I2C address':\n- wokwi-ds1307 Reference | Wokwi Docs (https://docs.wokwi.com/parts/wokwi-ds1307)\n  The I2C address of the DS1307 is 0x68.\n- In-Depth: Interface DS1307 RTC(Real Time Clock) Module with Arduino (https://lastminuteengineers.com/ds1307-rtc-arduino-tutorial/)\n  January 20, 2026 - The DS1307 RTC chip has a fixed I2C address of 0x68.\n- I2C address conficts with HD44780 (LCD) and DS1307 (RTC)? -- Solved - General Guidance - Arduino Forum (https://forum.arduino.cc/t/i2c-address-conficts-with-hd44780-lcd-and-ds1307-rtc-solved/520500)\n  April 15, 2018 - I have quite a stash of HD44780 (16 x 2 line LCD modules), and I've come to find out they all have a fixed I2C address of 0x37. This was all new to me, because I had thought on the ha\n- DS1307 | I2C Device Directory (https://i2cdevices.org/devices/ds1307)\n  DS1307: 64 x 8 Serial Real-Time Clock, I2C/TwoWire addresses: 0x68\n- Changing I2C address of DS1307 RTC - Raspberry Pi Forums (https://forums.raspberrypi.com/viewtopic.php?t=169599)\n  DougieLawson wrote:MPU9150 has pin# 9 AD0 to set the I²C Slave Address LSB. Set that pin HIGH and it will move from 0x68 to 0x69. Thank you. I see it in datasheet https://www.invensense.com/wp-content"}}
